<emphasis box="[418,503,1766,1785]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="730">Stegana</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[519,590,1765,1784]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="730">zhangi</emphasis>
Sidorenko
</taxonomicName>
from Hainan, China, 1–5, male; 6, 7, female: 1, epandrium (epand), surstylus (sur), and cercus (cerc) (lateral view); 2, sur (frontal view); 3, hypandrium (hypd) and gonopods (gon) (ventral view); 4, parameres (pm), aedeagus (aed), and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral view); 5, hypd, gon, pm, aed, and aed a (lateral view); 6, epiproct (epi) and cerc (dorsal view); 7. oviscapt (ovi) (viz. sternite VIII) and hypoproct (hypo) (ventral view). Scale bars = 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
